COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 736, L.D. 1866
1 4. Medical advice. Advocates providing services in accordance with this section are
2 prohibited from providing medical advice.'
3 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
4 number to read consecutively.
5 SUMMARY
66 This amendment replaces the bill. It requires the Department of Health and Human
77 Services to contract with the protection and advocacy agency for persons with disabilities
88 to carry out duties related to protecting the rights of individuals with serious mental illness
99 in both institutional and community settings.
